Hello,

I am on OSX and I often use ALT + <LEFT|RIGHT ARROW KEY> to jump back and forth through words.

Everything works fine when I&#x27;m normally writing a comment, but when I add italics to a word then the cursor can&#x27;t always jump backwards past that word. For example when I type this:

{code}
#!plaintext

This is an _example_
{code}

And then immediately hit ALT + LEFT ARROW KEY, the cursor will flick to the left-hand side of "example" and then back to the right-hand side immediately. Moving the cursor between typing the second &#x27;_&#x27; and trying to jump seems to work just fine.

